<!-- FAQ -->
<section id="faq" style="padding:90px 40px;background:var(--dark2);">
  <div style="text-align:center;">
    <span class="section-label">Questions?</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">Frequently <span>Asked Questions</span></h2>
  </div>
  <div style="max-width:800px;margin:40px auto 0;">
    <details style="border-bottom:1px solid #222;padding:20px 0;cursor:pointer;">
      <summary style="font-family:'Oswald',sans-serif;font-size:16px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;color:#fff;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;">What sets Pizza World apart? <span style="color:var(--red);font-size:20px;">+</span></summary>
      <p style="color:var(--gray);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;margin-top:14px;">Pizza World combines the world's finest gourmet pizzas with subs, calzones, salads, wings and traditional pizzas — all available for quick delivery or dine-in. We use only the freshest ingredients, real cheese, homemade sauce, and freshly baked dough. The entire system is designed for simplicity and customer convenience. We're changing the way the world thinks about pizza.</p>
    </details>
    <details style="border-bottom:1px solid #222;padding:20px 0;cursor:pointer;">
      <summary style="font-family:'Oswald',sans-serif;font-size:16px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;color:#fff;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;">What are the space requirements? <span style="color:var(--red);font-size:20px;">+</span></summary>
      <p style="color:var(--gray);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;margin-top:14px;">Delivery-focused units require 1,100 to 1,300 sq ft. Delivery plus sit-down restaurant units can go up to 2,400 sq ft. Typically located in strip centers (in-line or end caps) with good signage visibility, strong traffic counts, and proximity to residential areas, schools, and other customer sources.</p>
    </details>
    <details style="border-bottom:1px solid #222;padding:20px 0;cursor:pointer;">
      <summary style="font-family:'Oswald',sans-serif;font-size:16px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;color:#fff;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;">What training is provided? <span style="color:var(--red);font-size:20px;">+</span></summary>
      <p style="color:var(--gray);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;margin-top:14px;">It starts with our virtual training program that franchisees complete before ever stepping into a store. Then two weeks of hands-on training at a designated Pizza World location covering operations, computer systems, food preparation, delivery, daily management, and more. The virtual training platform stays available after opening — every new employee you hire goes through it too. Plus you get in-store assistance during your grand opening and ongoing support.</p>
    </details>
    <details style="border-bottom:1px solid #222;padding:20px 0;cursor:pointer;">
      <summary style="font-family:'Oswald',sans-serif;font-size:16px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;color:#fff;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;">How long does it take to open? <span style="color:var(--red);font-size:20px;">+</span></summary>
      <p style="color:var(--gray);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;margin-top:14px;">Construction typically takes 90 to 120 days, depending on location, store style, and size. Pizza World provides site and plan approval, construction and equipment specifications, design specifications, and approved supplier lists to streamline the process.</p>
    </details>
    <details style="border-bottom:1px solid #222;padding:20px 0;cursor:pointer;">
      <summary style="font-family:'Oswald',sans-serif;font-size:16px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;color:#fff;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;">Is financing available? <span style="color:var(--red);font-size:20px;">+</span></summary>
      <p style="color:var(--gray);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;margin-top:14px;">Yes — Pizza World is SBA approved, which means qualified candidates can access Small Business Administration financing through participating banks. You must demonstrate the financial ability to start, build, and manage the business.</p>
    </details>
    <details style="border-bottom:1px solid #222;padding:20px 0;cursor:pointer;">
      <summary style="font-family:'Oswald',sans-serif;font-size:16px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;color:#fff;list-style:none;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;">What ongoing fees are there? <span style="color:var(--red);font-size:20px;">+</span></summary>
      <p style="color:var(--gray);font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;margin-top:14px;">Royalty: 2.75% of net sales (the industry's lowest). Marketing: no required marketing fee — you invest what makes sense for your market. That's it — no hidden fees, no surprise charges. The franchise agreement runs for 10 years with a 10-year renewal option.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

